{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/bhyslop/projects/rbm_alpha_recipemuster","sessionId":"37405817-ab1b-4a15-a95b-2094a0c7da92","version":"2.1.69","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"ad4f3109969975c75","slug":"groovy-knitting-flurry","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Create two new single-architecture busybox vessel directories for the Recipe Bottle project. This is mechanical file creation following an existing pattern.\n\n## Context\n\nThe project has vessel directories under `rbev-vessels/`. Each vessel has:\n- `rbrv.env` — vessel identity and configuration (sourced as bash)\n- `Dockerfile` — build recipe\n- `proof.txt` — build context proof file\n\nThe `cloudbuild.json` is generated by the stitch function during inscribe — do NOT create it.\n\n## Reference: Existing busybox rbrv.env\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# (Apache 2.0 header)\n# Recipe Bottle Regime Vessel - BusyBox (Conjuring)\n\n# Core Identity\nRBRV_SIGIL=rbev-busybox\nRBRV_DESCRIPTION=\"Busybox small image for proving builds are working well cheaply\"\n\n# Vessel Mode\nRBRV_VESSEL_MODE=conjure\n\n# Conjuring Configuration\nRBRV_CONJURE_DOCKERFILE=\"${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}/${RBRV_SIGIL}/Dockerfile\"\nRBRV_CONJURE_BLDCONTEXT=\"${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}/${RBRV_SIGIL}\"\nRBRV_CONJURE_PLATFORMS=\"linux/amd64 linux/arm64 linux/arm/v7\"\nRBRV_CONJURE_BINFMT_POLICY=\"allow\"\n\n# eof\n```\n\n## Reference: Existing busybox Dockerfile\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM busybox:latest\nWORKDIR /app\nRUN adduser -D appuser\nUSER appuser\nCMD [\"echo\", \"BusyBox container is running!\"]\n```\n\n## Reference: proof.txt\n```\nPROOF OF BUILD CONTEXT\n```\n\n## Tasks\n\n### 1. Create `rbev-vessels/rbev-busybox-amd64/`\n\nCreate these files using the Write tool:\n\n**rbrv.env** — Use the EXACT same Apache 2.0 copyright header as the original busybox rbrv.env. Changes from original:\n- Comment line: `Recipe Bottle Regime Vessel - BusyBox AMD64 (Conjuring)`\n- `RBRV_SIGIL=rbev-busybox-amd64`\n- `RBRV_DESCRIPTION=\"Busybox single-arch amd64 vessel for SLSA v1.0 provenance validation\"`\n- `RBRV_CONJURE_PLATFORMS=\"linux/amd64\"` (single platform)\n- `RBRV_CONJURE_BINFMT_POLICY=\"deny\"` (native arch on CB workers, no QEMU needed)\n- All other fields identical but paths use `${RBRV_SIGIL}` so they auto-adjust\n\n**Dockerfile** — Identical to the busybox Dockerfile above (copy exactly)\n\n**proof.txt** — Identical: `PROOF OF BUILD CONTEXT\\n`\n\n### 2. Create `rbev-vessels/rbev-busybox-arm64/`\n\n**rbrv.env** — Same as amd64 but:\n- Comment line: `Recipe Bottle Regime Vessel - BusyBox ARM64 (Conjuring)`\n- `RBRV_SIGIL=rbev-busybox-arm64`\n- `RBRV_DESCRIPTION=\"Busybox single-arch arm64 vessel for SLSA v1.0 provenance validation\"`\n- `RBRV_CONJURE_PLATFORMS=\"linux/arm64\"`\n- `RBRV_CONJURE_BINFMT_POLICY=\"allow\"` (arm64 needs QEMU on amd64 CB workers)\n\n**Dockerfile** — Identical to busybox Dockerfile\n\n**proof.txt** — Identical: `PROOF OF BUILD CONTEXT\\n`\n\n### Important\n- Use absolute paths: `/Users/bhyslop/projects/rbm_alpha_recipemuster/rbev-vessels/rbev-busybox-amd64/` etc.\n- Do NOT create cloudbuild.json\n- Do NOT modify any existing files\n- Use the Write tool for all file creation\n"},"uuid":"78f0ebe8-3b12-47d0-b260-0ab8b5902cd9","timestamp":"2026-03-05T21:25:38.374Z"}
